name: clease-gui
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "clease-gui" %}
{% set version = "0.2.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b639a6779ad48396ee5473229f06d5e9b11be87a128057f91d7a6137dfdcd452

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  entry_points:
    - clease-gui=clease_gui.cli.main_cli:clease_gui_cli

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.7
    - ipython
    - jupyterlab
    - ipywidgets
    - clease >=0.11.6
    - pandas
    - matplotlib-base
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - click >=8.0.0
    - ase >=3.21
    - nglview
    - packaging
    - attrs

test:
  imports:
    - clease_gui
  requires:
    - pip
  commands:
    - pip check
    - clease-gui --version  # Test the CLI runs
    - clease-gui new  # Test we can copy the jupyter notebook

about:
  home: https://gitlab.com/computationalmaterials/clease-gui/
  license: MPL-2.0
  license_family: OTHER
  license_file: LICENSE.md
  summary: CLuster Expansion in Atomic Simulation Environment GUI

  description: |
    CLuster Expansion in Atomic Simulation Environment GUI
  doc_url: https://clease-gui.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://gitlab.com/computationalmaterials/clease-gui/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - atygesen
